title: Compiler Panic: Nightly: Trait Bounds?

labels.name: I-ICE
labels.description: Issue: The compiler panicked, giving an Internal Compilation Error (ICE) ❄️

labels.name: T-compiler
labels.description: Relevant to the compiler team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue.

body:
### Description Hi everyone! I found a compiler error in the nightly rustc compiler. I was unsure about the title but could not come up with a better phrase. I also tried to follow the [bug-minimization-patterns](http://blog.pnkfx.org/blog/2019/11/18/rust-bug-minimization-patterns/) to the best of my ability. Since this is my first contribution feel free to critique where I could do better. Thank you (the community) for developing and maintaining Rust! I really enjoy the language. ### Code ```Rust pub trait Stepper { fn do_step ( &mut self, y: &mut I, ) where for<'m>&'m I: IntoIterator; } fn helper ( mut y: I, t: &F, mut stepper: S, ) where S: Stepper, { stepper.do_step(&mut y, t); } ``` ### Cargo.toml ```Toml [package] name = "bug_report" description="compiler bug_report" authors = ["Jonas Pleyer"] version = "0.0.1" ``` ### Meta `rustc --version --verbose`: ``` rustc 1.65.0-nightly (748038961 2022-08-25) binary: rustc commit-hash: 7480389611f9d04bd34adf41a2b3029be4eb815e commit-date: 2022-08-25 host: x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu release: 1.65.0-nightly LLVM version: 15.0.0 ``` ### Error output ``` error: could not compile `bug_report` ```
